race.comment: PRESTIGE ICE (12) improved again, narrowly beaten this grade/trip at Lismore. Peaks and is will be fitter again. The one to beat. MAHMOA (14) rates well enough on his first-up Maiden win at Casino, where he led. He has plenty of scope for improvement. HIGH CLASS ROLLER (5) is in good hands and second up will appreciate the longer distance. He has the talent. GREEN MEADOWS (15) comes back in trip and placed second last time behind a dominant winner on the Gold Coast poly. He'd be a hope at best and is likely to show more today. FOREVER FORTUNE (3) improved to win his Maiden on the Gold Coast poly. Uses the inside gate and will be around the mark at a price.
